This truth became even more apparent to me after the transition of my mommy followed by my granddad and  parents of several BFFs. Tomorrow is not promised, heck, later today is not promised. 

This is the time to MOVE as if you don’t have any more time. Move into the unfamiliar, move into the uncomfortable, move without having all the answers, move holding on to faith knowing that you will be better because you moved…because you acted in courage…because you shot your shot…because you betted on yourself.

See you on the other side of your FAITH MOVE! Time is short, and the time is now! Act with a sense of urgency. ✨

Tomorrow!!! Bay Area!!! 

Ladies, I hope to see you at the She’s That Chick conference! It’s going UP! 🧡

It’s my AKAversary! I’ve hit another milestone in @akasorority1908 soaring to 5 years of service and sisterhood. Time really flies when you’re having fun and doing work that makes communities better. 

💕💚

I’ve had the privilege to serve locally, regionally and internationally from being Chaplain of my chapter, producing and co-chairing events for our region to media relations and branding for the sorority and our International President & CEO. And last but not least, witnessing the honorary membership induction of my boss. 

💕💚

I’m learning a lot and mastering even more. Looking forward to what the next 5 years has in store!
